annotationA: ATP binding; nucleoside diphosphate kinase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: nucleoside diphosphate phosphorylation; CTP biosynthetic process; UTP biosynthetic process; GTP biosynthetic process
annotationB: CTP synthase; Catalyzes the ATP-dependent amination of UTP to CTP with either L-glutamine or ammonia as the source of nitrogen. Constitutes the rate-limiting enzyme in the synthesis of cytosine nucleotides (By similarity). Isoform 1 is required for cytoophidium assembly in female germline cells
